      strAlbumCDart: 'https://www.theaudiodb.com/images/media/album/cdart/nothing-else-matters-4fb9b15aea36b.png',
      strAlbumSpine: null,
      strAlbum3DCase: null,
      strAlbum3DFlat: null,
      strAlbum3DFace: null,
      strAlbum3DThumb: null,
      strDescriptionEN: "\"Nothing Else Matters\" is an EP release of the power ballad by the American heavy metal band Metallica. It was released in 1992 as the third single from their self-titled fifth studio album, Metallica. The song peaked at number 11 on the Billboard Mainstream Rock Tracks chart as well as top-ten positions on many European charts. \"Nothing Else Matters\" was featured as a playable track in the music video game Guitar Hero: Metallica. The song has been covered over forty times.  The EP also includes live recordings of \"Enter Sandman\" and \"Harvester of Sorrows\" as well as the the song's demo which was also called \"Nothing Else Matters\" and was recorded in Lars Ulrich's home musical studio \"Dungeon\" on August 13, 1990.\n\n\n\n",
